Akenerji, TAV Havalimanlari, Turkcell: Turkey Equity Preview

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-04-28T06:23:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/akenerji-tav-havalimanlari-turkcell-turkey-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in  Turkey . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the
last close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 index (XU100)  fell 731.66, or
1.1 percent, to 67,792.69 yesterday.  Akenerji Elektrik Uretim AS (AKENR)  : The Turkish utility
owned by Czech Republic’s CEZ AS and Turkey’s Akkok Group may
complete the sale of its assets or have a short list of bidders
in June, Hurriyet reported, citing Akkok Chairman Mehmet Ali
Berkman. Akenerji rose 1 kurus, or 0.3 percent, to 3.81 liras.  TAV Havalimanlari Holding AS (TAVHL)  : The Turkish
airport operator held talks with Saudi banks to finance a bid to
develop Medina airport, Sabah reported. TAV dropped 4 kurus, or
0.5 percent, to 7.6 liras.  Turkcell Iletisim Hizmetleri AS (TCELL TI): Turkey’s
biggest mobile-phone company said first-quarter net income fell
21 percent from a year earlier to 330.1 million liras ($218
million). Profit was seen at 362 million liras, according to the
average estimate of nine analysts compiled by Bloomberg.
Separately, TeliaSonera AB said it filed a case with an Istanbul
court to convene a new meeting of shareholders to discuss
changes to Turkcell’s board and to approve a dividend payment.
Turkcell declined 2 kurus, or 0.2 percent, to 8.94 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
